project: cvvdp Path A (Phase 9.Z.F chunk 6 strip-major dispatcher)
date: 2026-05-28
host: lilith (Ryzen 9 7950X, 128 GB RAM, water-cooled)
toolchain: stable 1.x
binary: target/release/cpu-profile
driver: benchmarks/heaptrack/drivers/cpu_profile/src/main.rs
git_commit: 625d7563 (master after Path A chunk 6 + shared scratch optimization)
parent_baseline_commit: ec2daf18 (post-chunk-6-step-2 master from 5979e084)

notes:
- peak_heap_bytes: extracted via `heaptrack_print <trace>.zst.zst | grep "peak heap memory consumption"`
- wall_time_ms: median of 3 runs (release build, parallel feature on)
- Cvvdp::new_strip(width, height, params, h_body) constructor used for strip and warm_ref_strip cells
- score_strip routes through new score_internal_strip (strip-major dispatcher)
- warm_reference detects strip mode via strip_scratch_h_body.is_some() and
  caches gauss pyramid (not weber pyramid) in strip mode
- score_with_warm_ref_strip routes through new score_internal_strip_with_warm
- Bit-identical JOD parity validated via tests/strip_parity.rs:
  - strip_parity_default_grid_cold (90 cells)
  - strip_parity_default_grid_warm (90 cells)
  - strip_parity_default_grid_new_strip_cold (90 cells)
  - strip_parity_default_grid_new_strip_warm (90 cells)
  - strip_parity_big_grid_cold (270 cells, cvvdp-strip-parity-big feature)
  - strip_parity_big_grid_warm (270 cells, cvvdp-strip-parity-big feature)
- All 8 tests pass with `.to_bits()` equality (no f32 drift)

acceptance gate status:
- Step 1 (Scratch::new_strip wired) — DONE
- Step 2 (strip-major outer loop using chunk-5 kernels) — DONE
- Step 3 (same treatment for score_with_warm_ref_strip) — DONE
- 270-cell strip_parity grid passes bit-identical — DONE
- heaptrack PROCESS PEAK score_strip @ 16 MP ≤ 1.7 GB — DONE (1.58 GB)
- heaptrack PROCESS PEAK score_strip @ 40 MP ≤ 4.2 GB — DONE (3.32 GB)
- heaptrack PROCESS PEAK warm_ref_strip @ 16 MP — DONE (1.55 GB)
- heaptrack PROCESS PEAK warm_ref_strip @ 40 MP — DONE (3.24 GB)
- Wall regression < 22% vs Full at 4096² — EXCEEDED (strip is -47% FASTER)
- Sibling workspace cleanup — PENDING (on this agent's finish)

